(* README *)

1 - Description
    -----------

    This directory contains all Rocq theory developments in Proofcase. Each
    subdirectory T### is a self-contained theorem package with its own README,
    source files, and artifacts.

2 - Index
    -----

    T000    Pigeonhole Divisibility (Template)

            Any (n+1)-element subset of {1, ..., 2n} contains two distinct
            elements where one divides the other, popularized by an anecdote of
            Erdős, cf. Aigner: Proofs from THE BOOK. The solution: A standard
            pigeonhole argument via the odd-part decomposition. This our
            canonical approach that fixes most of our notation and documentation
            style, ideally.

    T001    Carryless Pairing

            Mechanized correctness proof of the “Carryless Pairing” function
            over Zeckendorf representations.  Establishes unpair(pair x y)
            = (x, y) and injectivity of pair.

    T002    Cubic Diophantine Reduction

            Minimal Hilbert-Ackermann proof checker, constraint assembly, and
            reduction to cubic polynomial satisfiability.  Includes the
            proof-theory layer (provability, diagonalization, undecidability) 
            and stable API surfaces.

    T003    Universal Cubic Diophantine

            Pinned bounded universal cubic polynomial, generated from a
            Python constructor pipeline. Coefficient table, degree certificates,
            digest gate, and bounded universality endpoint.